He brought the Black unemployment rate for African Americans from 16.8 percent, due to the horror of President George W. Bush to 7.8 percent by January 2017.
The poverty rate for African Americans fell faster in 2015 than in any year since 1999 — falling 2.1 percentage points, resulting in 700,000 fewer African Americans in poverty.
